The paper proposes a new blockchain consensus protocol that aims for simplicity while achieving excellent throughput and decentralization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
